# The Email Spam Detection project is fully set up in the email_spam_detector/ directory!

# Here is what was created:

# README.md & requirements.txt: For setup and environment instructions.
# src/download_data.py: A fallback script to automatically download the SpamAssassin dataset and create data/emails.csv.
# src/preprocess.py: Text cleaning logic with nltk (removes stopwords, lemmatizes, removes HTML, URLs, etc.).
# src/train.py: Main script to vectorise the text (TF-IDF), train 4 models (Naive Bayes, Logistic Regression, Linear SVM, Random Forest), print comparison metrics, plot all the requested graphs, and save the best model + vectorizer to the models/ directory using joblib.
# src/predict.py: Model loading and inference script.
# app.py: The complete Gradio web UI.
# notebook.ipynb: The Jupyter Notebook providing a walkthrough and EDA.
# How to use it:
# Install Requirements: Open your terminal and navigate to the project directory, then run:
# bash
# cd email_spam_detector
# pip install -r requirements.txt
# Download the Data:
# bash
# python src/download_data.py
# Train the Models and generate the plots:
# bash
# python src/train.py
# (This will create plots in the plots/ folder and models in models/)
# Launch the UI:
# bash
# python app.py
# Feel free to run the commands directly in your terminal, or let me know if you would like me to trigger any of them for you!